{"image_id": "CINF_2011_page_66", "image_size": [1275, 1650], "ocr": [{"text": "Cincinnati Financial Corporation – 2011 10-K - 64", "bbox": [401.3, 1592.9, 780.9, 1615.2]}, {"text": "trends may be reflected for this line of business sooner than for some other commercial lines. Higher new", "bbox": [90.0, 58.4, 1064.7, 86.0]}, {"text": "business written premiums from agencies accounted for $7 million of the $20 million increase in net", "bbox": [90.0, 82.4, 1009.0, 110.0]}, {"text": "written premiums.", "bbox": [90.0, 106.4, 260.3, 134.0]}, {"text": "The 2011 total loss and loss expense ratio rose 6.7 percentage points, largely due to a 3.6 point increase", "bbox": [90.0, 136.4, 1062.4, 164.0]}, {"text": "from higher large losses. The refined line of business allocation process for loss expenses contributed", "bbox": [90.0, 160.4, 1033.2, 188.0]}, {"text": "1.7 percentage points to the 2011 total loss and loss expense ratio and also contributed to the increase in", "bbox": [90.0, 184.4, 1066.0, 212.0]}, {"text": "the ratio for the current accident year before catastrophe losses.", "bbox": [90.0, 208.4, 692.0, 236.0]}, {"text": "The 2011 current accident year loss and loss expense ratio before catastrophe losses rose 4.5 percentage", "bbox": [90.0, 238.7, 1076.2, 266.3]}, {"text": "points, compared with accident year 2010, primarily due to a rise in loss cost trends that might relate to the", "bbox": [90.0, 262.7, 1076.2, 290.3]}, {"text": "improving economy, combined with pricing that improved more slowly. Non-catastrophe weather losses also", "bbox": [90.0, 286.4, 1089.9, 314.1]}, {"text": "had a slight adverse effect on the ratio.", "bbox": [90.0, 310.4, 460.5, 338.1]}, {"text": "Workers’ Compensation", "bbox": [90.0, 339.9, 354.2, 371.9]}, {"text": "(Dollars in millions)", "bbox": [51.4, 376.8, 157.4, 393.8]}, {"text": "2011", "bbox": [577.3, 395.2, 609.8, 416.7]}, {"text": "2010", "bbox": [685.9, 395.9, 718.4, 417.0]}, {"text": "2009", "bbox": [794.5, 395.9, 827.